<article>
    <h1>How well do you know your ex&#xAD;penses?</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201206/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-06"><time>2020-12-06</time></a>
        - <span>INVEST</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Sun­day Times’ In­vest and OCBC Bank have come up with a sim­ple quiz to test how well you know your ex­penses.</p>
    <p>The quiz asks you to pick one of three pos­si­ble sce­nar­ios on how you would like to spend your re­tire­ment. These are:</p>
    <p>LIFE­STYLE A</p>
    <p>• Have meals mostly at home, hawker cen­tres or food­courts</p>
    <p>• Live in an HDB flat, no do­mes­tic helper and use pub­lic trans­port</p>
    <p>• If sick, seek treat­ment at poly­clin­ics or gov­ern­ment hos­pi­tals</p>
    <p>• Travel to nearby coun­tries</p>
    <p>for hol­i­days twice a year</p>
    <p>LIFE­STYLE B</p>
    <p>• Have meals mostly at hawker cen­tres, food­courts or restau­rants • Live in an HDB flat, have a part-time helper, take cabs or have a car</p>
    <p>• If sick, seek treat­ment at pri­vate clin­ics or gov­ern­ment hos­pi­tals • Travel to nearby coun­tries for hol­i­days three times a year</p>
    <p>LIFE­STYLE C</p>
    <p>• Have meals mostly at</p>
    <p>restau­rants</p>
    <p>• Live in a pri­vate home, have a do­mes­tic helper and own a car</p>
    <p>• If sick, seek treat­ment at pri­vate clin­ics or pri­vate hos­pi­tals</p>
    <p>• Travel to far­away coun­tries for hol­i­days twice a year</p>
    <p>• Spend on life­style and</p>
    <p>well­ness-re­lated ac­tiv­i­ties</p>
    <p>Af­ter that, you pick the monthly bud­get that is needed and see if you get the es­ti­mated costs cor­rect.</p>
    <p>Ms Tan Siew Lee, OCBC’s head of wealth man­age­ment here, says: “Sin­ga­pore­ans gen­er­ally don’t un­der­stand their cur­rent fi­nan­cial sit­u­a­tion well, and their un­der­stand­ing of fu­ture fi­nan­cial pro­jec­tions is even hazier.</p>
    <p>“We hope this quiz will spur peo­ple to come to that eureka mo­ment that they should start their fi­nan­cial plan­ning early and con­sult a pro­fes­sional ad­viser. The sooner, the bet­ter.”</p>
    <p>Read­ers can take the quiz at str.sg/in­vest-quiz, or by scan­ning the QR code.</p>

